listData.name: Pension Advantage
listData.description: Receive a pension and need an everyday account? Pension Advantage delivers you the freedom to bank how and when you want and the ability to minimise or avoid transaction fees altogether.

features.additionalInfo: Use your Visa Debit Card to shop online, in-person and access cash at ATMs.

eligibility.additionalInfo: To be eligible for the Pension Advantage product you must receive an Aged, Australian War Veterans or Disability Pension from the Department of Social Security (Centrelink) or Department of Veteran Affairs and be a holder of a current Pensioner Concession Card or Repatriation Health Card. For joint accounts, at least one of the account holders must satisfy this criteria to be eligible.

fees.name: STAFF_ASSISTED_TRANSACTIONS
fees.additionalInfo: For transactions performed at a Retail Store or through our Contact Centre

fees.name: SELF_SERVICE_INTERNET_BANKING_TRANSACTIONS
fees.additionalInfo: Applies for each transaction performed from or to your Bank of us account. These include one off or regular (Periodical Payment) transfers and BPAY transactions.

fees.name: SELF_SERVICE_EFTPOS_TRANSACTIONS
fees.additionalInfo: Self-service EFTPOS transactions mean a transaction you make to purchase goods, purchase goods and withdraw cash, or withdraw cash via EFTPOS facilities.

fees.name: BANK@POST_WITHDRAWAL_FEE
fees.additionalInfo: This fee applies where you make a cash withdrawal via Australia Post offices displaying the Bank@Post symbol. The fee is debited to your account at the end of the month in which the fee is incurred.

fees.name: OVERSEAS_DEBIT_CARD_REPLACEMENT_FEE
fees.additionalInfo: Applies where you request the emergency replacement through VISA International of your VISA Debit card that is lost or stolen. The fee is debited to your account at the time of your request for a replacement card.

fees.name: OVERSEAS_CARD_TRANSACTION_FEE
fees.additionalInfo: Applies to all cash advances and retail purchase transactions made in currencies other than Australian dollars. The fee is added to the total transaction amount debited to your account in Australian dollars.
